Baidu Inc's Subsidiary Signs Definitive Agreement With Renren For Strategic Investment In Nuomi
Friday, 23 Aug 2013 04:40am EDT
Baidu, Inc and Renren Inc (Renren), a real-name social networking Internet platform in China, jointly announced that Baidu Holdings Limited, a subsidiary of Baidu, and Renren have entered into a definitive agreement (the Agreement), pursuant to which Baidu Holdings Limited will acquire a certain number of newly issued ordinary shares of Nuomi Holdings Inc., a wholly-owned subsidiary of Renren, representing approximately 59% of the equity interest in Nuomi, for a purchase price of USD160 million in cash. Subject to the satisfaction or waiver of the closing conditions provided in the Agreement, the parties expect to close this acquisition in the fourth quarter of 2013.Â 
